statement.tex:
\text{For what value of k would }\\
f(x) = \begin{cases}
  kx + 1, x\leq\pi, \\
  \cos x, x\gt \pi
\end{cases}
\\ \text{be continuous at }x=\pi?

options.tex:
\begin{align}
  \lim_{x\to \pi^-}f(x) &= \lim_{x\to \pi^-}kx+1=k\pi + 1 \\
  \lim_{x\to \pi^+}f(x) & \lim_{x\to \pi^+}\cos x = -1 \\
  f(\pi) &= k\pi + 1
\end{align}
\\ \text{And hence, for continuity at }x=\pi \\
\begin{align}
  k\cdot\pi + 1 &= -1 \implies k = -\dfrac{2}{\pi}
\end{align}
